    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Counsel to Reserved, Dictatorial Parents</strong>&mdash;There is danger of both parents and teachers commanding and dictating too much, while they fail to come sufficiently into social relation with their children or scholars. They often hold themselves too much reserved and exercise their authority in a cold, unsympathizing manner which cannot win the hearts of their children and pupils. If they would gather the children close to them and show that they love them, and would manifest an interest in all their efforts and even in their sports, sometimes even being a child among children, they would make the children very happy and would gain their love and win their <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"193\"></span> confidence. And the children would sooner respect and love the authority of their parents and teachers.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"3T 134.1\" data-link=\"119.620\">Testimonies for the Church 3:134, 135</span>.</span></a></sup>",
